<HEADLINE>
<P>
GORBACHEV'S LEADERSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In your editorial "One Who Made a Revolution" (Feb. 8) you correctly praise 
Gorbachev for "honestly defin(ing) the -- conditions facing his country; 
begin(ning) the slow and painful effort to the unshackle the regime from the 
corpse of failed policies and irrelevant ideologies, not least those of the 
Cold War." 
</P>
<P>
I can't help but wonder how long it will take the U.S. to acquire the same 
quality of leadership, foresight and willingness to accommodate to a changing 
world with challenges of environmental degradation, overpopulation, energy 
resource depletion and poverty. 
</P>
<P>
ADOLPH B. AMSTER 
</P>
<P>
Ridgecrest 
</P>
</TEXT>
