<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: CHULA VISTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A San Diego man has died of injuries he received in a hit-and-run accident that 
killed another man, Chula Vista police said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Edward Maher, 31, died Sunday of multiple injuries, a coroner's deputy said. 
</P>
<P>
Maher and 23-year-old Raymond Jarvey were playing pool in Smitty's Tavern at 
119 Broadway when a fight broke out shortly after 1:45 a.m. Saturday, police 
Sgt. Richard Coulson said. The bartender told the two men to leave and they 
continued the fight outside, armed with pool cues. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses saw the men lying in the street fighting when a car traveling about 
35 m.p.h. ran over them, Coulson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
