<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIRA COSTA, NO. 1 IN NATION, TO OPEN VOLLEYBALL SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROB FERNAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mira Costa High's boys volleyball team, ranked No. 1 in the nation by USA 
Today, will open the season at 7:30 Friday night with a non-league match at 
Loyola High, west of downtown Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
This marks the 11th consecutive season the Mustangs have opened against Loyola. 
</P>
<P>
Mira Costa leads the series, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
Coach Mike Cook's squad returns three starters from last year's team that came 
within one victory of a CIF title and a perfect season. The Mustangs lost to 
Corona del Mar in the Southern Section 4-A final to finish 21-1. 
</P>
<P>
Mira Costa will center its attack around 6-foot-4 setter Canyon Ceman, 6-5 
middle blocker Patrick Ivie and 6-4 outside hitter David Swatik, a first-team 
All-CIF choice last season. 
</P>
<P>
The three seniors, along with 6-7 middle blocker Mike Ashenfelter, are all 
being heavily recruited by major colleges, Cook said. 
</P>
<P>
Outside hitter Mark Shoptaw, a 6-3 junior, is the top varsity newcomer. 
</P>
<P>
"I call them the Magnificent Five," Cook said of his leading players. "We're 
just trying to find another one to fill out a starting lineup." 
</P>
<P>
After Friday's match, Mira Costa resumes play March 9 at Palisades, one of the 
top teams in the L.A. City Section. ROB FERNAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
