<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: FITZGERALD NAMED DEFENSIVE ASSISTANT WITH TAMPA BAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jeff Fitzgerald, a former player and coach at Burroughs High, has been named a 
defensive assistant with the Tampa Bay Buccaneers of the NFL. 
</P>
<P>
Fitzgerald, an All-Southern Section linebacker in 1978 while at Burroughs, 
spent two years playing football at Valley and Pierce colleges before attending 
Oregon State in 1980. 
</P>
<P>
Fitzgerald returned to Los Angeles in 1981 and completed his undergraduate 
education at Cal State Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
He spent the past four years as a graduate assistant at Alabama. 
</P>
<P>
The Lanark Recreation Center in Canoga Park will stage a "Fight Night" amateur 
boxing exhibition Friday at 7 p.m. It is open to amateur youth and adults, 
independent and club boxers. Registration is $7 per boxer. Weigh-in starts at 
5:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Information: 818-883-1503. 
</P>
