143 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
PLANNED PARENTHOOD GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A $25,00 allocation to Pasadena Planned Parenthood, reluctantly approved in 
December by the city Board of Directors, will not be needed this fiscal year 
after all. 
</P>
<P>
City directors were informed Tuesday that the family planning agency will 
receive its full state funding to operate a clinic at 1045 N. Lake Ave. 
</P>
<P>
Although Gov. George Deukmejian had cut statewide family planning funds last 
year, the Legislature restored the money in a bill passed in January. 
</P>
<P>
However, if Deukmejian pursues funding cuts already proposed for the next 
fiscal year, Pasadena Planned Parenthood could draw on a second $25,000 
allocation approved by directors in December. 
</P>
<P>
After the board approved the appropriations to Planned Parenthood and two other 
social service agencies, it created a committee that is devising a city policy 
governing aid to nonprofit agencies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA030190-0082 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 182992 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 1, 1990, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Long Beach; Part J; Page 2; Column 3 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
