<P>
2 FINALISTS IN MUSIC CONTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Crossroads School students will be competing for a scholarship and trophy 
next week in the Music Center's second annual Spotlight Awards. 
</P>
<P>
Michelle Kim and Anders Martinson, students of the Santa Monica school, along 
with Wendy Chen of South Pasadena, are finalists in the instrumental music 
category of the competition. 
</P>
<P>
Martinson, a pianist, will play a Chopin opus and Kim, a violinist, will 
perform a piece by Henri Wieniawski in the finals Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Eight other young artists are competing in vocal music, dance and drama 
categories. A panel of judges that includes Walter Mirisch, Ernest Fleischmann, 
Gerald Arpino and Bella Lewitzky will choose a total of five winners, who will 
each get a $5,000 cash scholarship from the Music Center. 
</P>
<P>
The competition is the culmination of a process that began last October, with 
387 people from throughout Southern California applying. 
</P>
