<P>
MALATHION MEETING PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mayor William Thomson will try to set up a meeting in late March among Southern 
California city officials opposed to malathion aerial spraying. 
</P>
<P>
The Pasadena Board of Directors voted Tuesday to organize the meeting as a 
follow-up to its action last week banning low-altitude flights over Pasadena. 
City police helicopters were sent out to enforce the ordinance against 
helicopter pilots spraying malathion. The action prompted a meeting with Gov. 
George Deukmejian. 
</P>
<P>
Thomson said he would try to call a meeting March 22 or 23, when more than 300 
city officials and staff members are expected to attend a Southern California 
Assn. of Governments meeting at the Pasadena Hilton Hotel. 
</P>
