</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Downey City Council on Tuesday night unanimously approved a resolution 
calling for a halt to aerial malathion spraying to combat the crop-destroying 
Mediterranean fruit fly. 
</P>
<P>
About 25 sign-carrying residents demonstrated outside City Hall before the 
council meeting. 
</P>
