<HEADLINE>
<P>
PICK OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Pasadena Modelers Society will hold a major regional model building contest 
and exhibition at the Pasadena Center, 300 E. Green St., from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. 
Sunday. Admission is $3 for adults and free for children under 12 who are with 
their parents. 
</P>
<P>
The highlight of the exhibit will be a display of Soviet small arms put on by 
the Foreign Military Intelligence Group of the National Training Center at Ft. 
Irwin. The exhibit, a 10-by-20-foot mural display, includes weapons ranging 
from the AK-47 to the RPG-7 (rocket-propelled grenade) and 1/10-scale models of 
Soviet armored vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
Among exhibits will be a 1/35-scale model of a Sherman tank and accessories 
used in World War II, above. The California Highway Patrol will display the 
Ford Mustang high-speed pursuit car with its 5.0-liter V-8 engine that is used 
on outlying freeways. 
</P>
<P>
The model building competition will include the categories of armor, aircraft, 
ships, science fiction, dioramas, figures and automobiles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Model tank 
</P>
