immediate halt to offensive operations by the Sandinista army. The cease-fire 
call came hours after election victor Violeta Barrios de Chamorro -- helped to 
a press conference, left, in the wake of a knee injury -- joined the government 
in urging the U.S.-backed rebels to disarm at once. A1 Associated Press; Photo, 
Chamorro signals to supporters after press conference Wednesday. J. ALBERT DIAZ 
/ Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
