<P>
ISRAELI DEPLORES CONVENT DELAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Israeli Foreign Minister Moshe Arens called for the temporary relocation of 
Roman Catholic nuns whose convent at Auschwitz sparked a Polish-Jewish dispute. 
</P>
<P>
Poland's Roman Catholic Church has begun construction of an interfaith prayer 
and dialogue center at the former Nazi death camp that will also contain a 
cloister for 16 Carmelite nuns. But Jewish leaders are unhappy with delays in 
moving the nuns. The construction is expected to take about 18 months. Arens 
ended an official visit to Poland after signing an agreement restoring full 
diplomatic ties with Poland after a 23-year break. 
</P>
</TEXT>
