DOMESTIC ISSUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Today I was watching Congress on TV. (When) Robert Dornan spoke . . . he said 
he was disappointed in the previous speakers because they addressed only 
domestic issues. 
</P>
<P>
Dornan proceeded to say that this was one of the greatest days in U.S. history 
