<P>
2 STREETS TO BE USED FOR HAULING PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Large tractor-trailers will be using Birch Street and Brea Boulevard to carry 
dirt and rocks to a construction project until the end of March. 
</P>
<P>
Trucks will use the streets from Monday through Friday during the day, 
traveling west on Birch and south on Brea to the southwest corner of 
Bastanchury Road, where the rubble is being used for a development there, 
according to Assistant City Engineer John Hogan. 
</P>
<P>
A street sweeper will operate continuously to keep the streets clean and dust 
to a minimum. 
</P>
<P>
The material comes from the Laurel Creek project at Birch and Ash Street and 
the old high school site on Birch. 
</P>
