<P>
New Financial Agency Proposed: State Sen. Dan McCorquodale (D-San Jose) 
introduced legislation that would put banks, savings and loans, credit unions 
and other financial institutions under the supervision of a single state 
agency. He said combining the departments of banking, corporations, real estate 
and savings and loan into a Department of Financial Institutions would provide 
better enforcement. 
</P>
