<TEXT>
<P>
Dart Group Settles SEC Complaint: Corporate raider Herbert Haft's Dart Group 
settled an SEC complaint alleging that it had acted as an investment company 
because it made large profits from the sale of stocks in a series of takeover 
bids for retailing companies. Without admitting or denying wrongdoing, the 
Landover, Md., company agreed in effect not to buy and sell securities as its 
primary business unless it registers as an investment company. The SEC accused 
Dart Group in a civil complaint in Washington federal court of violating 
securities laws by acting as an unregistered investment firm. 
</P>
