<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: CONSPIRACY COUNT AGAINST BUCKEY WILL BE 
DROPPED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A single count of conspiracy will be dropped against Manhattan Beach McMartin 
Pre-School defendant Ray Buckey, prosecutors said Wednesday, adding that they 
expect to proceed on the remaining 12 counts against him, with testimony from 
five children. 
</P>
<P>
"We do not intend to proceed with the conspiracy count, which will shorten the 
trial considerably and strengthen our case," Deputy Dist. Atty. 
</P>
<P>
Joe Martinez told reporters after a 90-minute closed-door meeting with defense 
attorney Danny Davis and the new judge assigned to the trial, Los Angeles 
Superior Court Judge Stanley Weisberg. 
</P>
<P>
Buckey, 31, and his mother, Peggy McMartin Buckey, were acquitted in January of 
53 child molestation charges involving the now-defunct school. Jurors 
deadlocked on 13 other counts against Buckey and a new trial was ordered. 
Prosecutors have until Tuesday to file their amended complaint, and the trial 
is expected to begin Wednesday on schedule. 
</P>
</TEXT>
