<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION BASKETBALL CHAMPIONSHIPS; 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS 3-AA; 
</P>
<P>
BREA-OLINDA BEATS PALOS VERDES, 50-33 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KOLLEN LONG, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brea-Olinda High won its second consecutive Southern Section girls' basketball 
championship with a 50-33 victory over Palos Verdes Wednesday in the 3-AA title 
game at Cal Poly Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
Brea-Olinda (30-0) won the 3-A and state Division III championships last 
season. 
</P>
<P>
Guard Aimee McDaniel scored 15 points and Tammy Blackburn held Palos Verdes' 
top scorer, Lisa Humphreys, to five points, as Brea-Olinda won its 51st 
consecutive game. It is the second-longest streak by a girls' Southern Section 
team. Riverside Poly has the record with 84. 
</P>
<P>
Humphreys came into the game averaging 15.4 points. She did not make a field 
goal until midway through the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Palos Verdes (27-5) was led by 6-foot-3 sophomore Monique Morehouse, who scored 
13 points. 
</P>
<P>
Despite building a 23-13 halftime lead, the Lady Cats hardly resembled the team 
that dominated three previous playoff opponents by an average of 30 points. 
They made only 10 of 25 first-half shots. But they pulled away at the start of 
the fourth quarter with a 9-0 run. 
</P>
<P>
Defensively, Brea-Olinda showed the form that held its playoff opponents to an 
average of 36 points. 
</P>
<P>
Palos Verdes made four of 25 shots in the first half. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
