<P>
LOTTERY JACKPOT AT $12 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nobody had all six winning numbers in the mid-week California "Lotto 6-49" 
game, so the $5.46-million jackpot rolls over to build a Saturday jackpot as 
rich as $12 million, lottery officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
The numbers picked in the twice-weekly game were 26, 23, 5, 38, 30, 47 and the 
bonus number, 40. 
</P>
<P>
There were four tickets with five correct numbers plus the bonus number, each 
worth $375,083 shares of a $1.7-million prize pool. Another 221 with five of 
six will share $773,000, each receiving $3,497. 
</P>
<P>
There were 12,395 tickets with four of six, each worth $56 shares of a $702,000 
prize pool. 
</P>
