<P>
MOSCOW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Coal miners in the Ukrainian city of Donetsk staged a warning strike at 21 
mines today to demand the resignation of the entire regional Communist Party 
leadership, participants and news reports said. 
</P>
<P>
Seven miners were in the third day of a hunger strike in front of the party 
headquarters in the city of 1.1 million people to back demands that party 
bosses quit en masse, Radio Moscow's Interfax news service said. 
</P>
<P>
But the party brass refused to consider resigning until a regional party 
conference scheduled for April 6-7, Interfax said. 
</P>
<P>
The Ukraine's entire Donbass coal belt was shut down for more than a week last 
summer as part of a nationwide coal strike by miners demanding better pay and 
improved working and living conditions. 
