<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
'89 HOLIDAY BOWL RICHEST EVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Penn State and Brigham Young University each received more than $1 million from 
the Holiday Bowl, the largest payout in the bowl's 12-year history. 
</P>
<P>
The Nittany Lions defeated BYU, 50-39, in the Dec. 29 game at San Diego's Jack 
Murphy Stadium. Fifteen Holiday Bowl records were set during the contest. 
</P>
<P>
The total payout of $2,018,076 was divided evenly between the schools for 
checks of $1,009,038. 
</P>
<P>
The bowl's previous highest team payout was in 1988, when Oklahoma State and 
Wyoming each received $907,613. 
</P>
</TEXT>
