<P>
TOURNAMENT OPENS WITH 2 ACES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MIYAZAKI, Japan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two golfers aced holes today as the Japan PGA Tour opened with the Daiichi 
Fodosan Cup tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Hajime Meshiai scored a hole-in-one on the 180-yard fifth hole en route to a 
7-under-par 65 and the first-round lead. 
</P>
<P>
Norio Mikami aced the 140-yard seventh hole and shot a 66. 
</P>
<P>
Meshiai, whose only victory last year came in June, had seven birdies and two 
bogeys to go with his ace on the 6,430-yard, par-72 Miyazaki International Golf 
Club course. 
</P>
