<P>
Mark Rodenhauser, a punt snapper for the Minnesota Vikings last season, was 
signed today by the San Diego Chargers as a Plan B free agent. 
</P>
<P>
Rodenhauser appeared in 16 games last year, registering five tackles and four 
assists. He joined Minnesota as a free agent after one season with the Chicago 
Bears, who waived him before the 1988 season. In 1987, he played in 10 games 
for the Bears, including starts in all three strike games. 
